Orbit Onboarding is a centralized onboarding and knowledge management platform built using Spring Boot, Spring Security, JWT authentication, PostgreSQL, and Spring Data JPA. The application allows users to register, access training modules, read knowledge articles, and track onboarding progress. I implemented layered architecture with controllers for handling requests, services for business logic, repositories for database interaction, and entities mapped using JPA. Security is handled through JWT-based stateless authentication with BCrypt password encryption. Module progress tracking uses relational mapping and database constraints to ensure users complete modules only once. Swagger was integrated for API testing and documentation.
USER role

A normal employee/new joiner using the onboarding platform.

Typical actions:

Register and log in
View training modules
Read knowledge articles
Search articles
Mark modules as completed
View personal progress

Flow:

USER
   ↓
Login
   ↓
Read onboarding content
   ↓
Complete modules
   ↓
Track progress %

Example:

A new employee joins the company:

John
 ↓
Reads "Git Workflow"
 ↓
Reads "Coding Standards"
 ↓
Completes Module 1
 ↓
Progress becomes 25%
ADMIN role

Admin is responsible for maintaining the onboarding content and system data.

Specific actions:

Training Module Management

Create modules:

POST /api/training/module

Update modules:

PUT /api/training/module/{id}

Delete modules:

DELETE /api/training/module/{id}

Example:

Admin creates:

Module:
"Spring Boot Basics"

Description:
"Introduction to Spring Boot"

Estimated hours:
3
Knowledge Article Management

Create articles:

POST /api/knowledge

Update articles:

PUT /api/knowledge/{id}

Delete articles:

DELETE /api/knowledge/{id}

Example:

Title:
Git Workflow

Category:
GIT_WORKFLOW

Content:
Branch naming rules and pull request process
Manage onboarding content

Admins act as content owners.

They decide:

Learning sequence (moduleOrder)
Estimated duration
Documentation
Team guidelines
